Build
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Un tar atmi++-0.2.tar.gz and run:
	prompt$ cd atmi++-0.2
	prompt$ configure
	prompt$ make

This will build:
- lib/libatmi++.a
- lib/libatmiutl++.a
- bin/tptest
- bin/qtest
- app/SIMPSERV
- app/SIMPSERV++

If you have installed doxygen (http://www.doxygen.org/ then you can build 
an online documentation of atmi++'s classes and sample code.
  prompt$ make doxygen

Autoconf
-------------------------------------------------------------------

Autoconf was usage reminder:
  prompt$ autoscan

Rename and taylor configure.scan into configure.ac. Run autoheader:
  promtp$ autoheader

Create configure script
  prompt$ autoconf

Voila you should be done.

If you need more so to http://www.gnu.org/software/autoconf/

